cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR

This paper deals with visual localization, which is a subfield of computer vision and robotics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely categories. The paper also uses semantic information, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method proposed in the paper involves scoring and weighting, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with 3D models and structures, which could fall under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR).
